## Context
Agent UX review found two high-severity discoverability gaps:

1. `make ticket-ready` is not mentioned in any agent-facing doc
   (AGENTS.md, on-start.md, start-ticket.md). An agent has no
   path from "I should find work" to the command.

2. Neither start-ticket.md nor celebrate.md tells agents HOW to
   transition Status or write log entries. The format lives only
   in the spec, not in the runbooks agents actually consult.

Also: Blocked-by forward references require committing blocking
tickets first — undocumented ordering constraint.

## Actions
1. AGENTS.md wave cycle "Select" step: add
   "Run `make ticket-ready` to list unblocked open tickets."
2. start-ticket.md: after creating worktree, add instructions to
   set `Status: doing`, append log entry, commit immediately
3. celebrate.md: add instruction to set `Status: closed` with
   log entry
4. new-ticket.md: add note about commit ordering when using
   Blocked-by (commit blocking tickets first)
5. Add `make ticket-ready` output to include filename
   (already has it in JSON mode, add to human-readable mode)

## Exit criteria
- An agent reading only AGENTS.md + runbooks can find, claim,
  and close tickets without consulting the spec
